9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 488, L.D. 746, “An Act to Authorize a
10 Local Option Sales Tax on Short-term Lodging to Fund Municipalities and Affordable
11 Housing”
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1822 by striking out all of subsection 2 (page 1, lines 9
13 to 12 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
14 '2. Authorization to impose local option sales tax. A municipality by referendum
15 conducted pursuant to subsection 8 may impose a local option sales tax of 2% on the value
16 of rental of living quarters in any hotel, rooming house and tourist and trailer camp,
17 including casual rentals.
18 A. A local option sales tax may not be imposed in the unorganized territory.
19 B. A local option sales tax may be imposed only on a year-round basis. A municipality
20 may not adopt a seasonal or part-year local option sales tax.'
21 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1822 in subsection 3 in the last line (page 1, line 15 in
22 L.D.) by striking out the following: "section" and inserting the following: 'sections 1764
23 and'
24 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1822 in subsection 3 in the last line (page 1, line 15 in
25 L.D.) by inserting after the following: "1811." the following: 'A taxpayer who reports sales
26 tax collected on casual rentals on that taxpayer's individual income tax return pursuant to
27 section 1951-A, subsection 3 is not required to collect and remit local option sales tax.'
28 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1822 in subsection 5 in the last line (page 1, line 22 in
29 L.D.) by striking out the following: "Part." and inserting the following: 'Part, and sourcing
30 determinations must be made pursuant to section 1819.'
31 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1822 in subsection 9 in the 3rd line (page 2, line 16 in
32 L.D.) by striking out the following: "9" and inserting the following: '8'
33 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1822 in subsection 9 in the last line (page 2, line 20 in
34 L.D.) by striking out the following: "2026" and inserting the following: '2027'
